  "A small business tracks monthly expenses: rent (r), wages (w), and supplies (s). Total expenses are $10,000. Wages are three times supplies. Rent is $2,000 more than supplies. What are the monthly wages?": "",
  "$5,400": "",
  "$4,800": "",
  "$6,000": "",
  "$3,600": "",
  "r + w + s = 10000, w = 3s, r = s + 2000. Substitute: (s + 2000) + 3s + s = 10000, 5s = 8000, s = 1600. Wages = 3(1600) = $4,800.": "",
  "A farmer plants three crops on 200 acres. Corn takes twice as many acres as soybeans. Wheat uses 40 more acres than soybeans. How many acres of corn?": "",
  "70": "",
  "60": "",
  "100": "",
  "80": "",
  "c + w + s = 200, c = 2s, w = s + 40. Substitute: 2s + (s + 40) + s = 200, 4s = 160, s = 40. Corn = 2(40) = 80 acres.": "",
  "Three friends invest $12,000 total. The first invests $2,000 more than the second. The third invests half of what the first invests. How much does the first friend invest?": "",
  "$5,000": "",
  "$5,600": "",
  "a + b + c = 12000, a = b + 2000, c = a/2. Since a = b + 2000 and c = (b + 2000)/2: b + 2000 + b + (b + 2000)/2 = 12000, 2.5b + 3000 = 12000, b = 3600. First friend = $5,600.": "",
  "A factory produces items A ($10 profit), B ($15 profit), and C ($20 profit). They produce 100 units total. Item B production exceeds A by 20 units. Item C is 10 fewer than A. What is the total profit?": "",
  "$1,350": "",
  "$1,250": "",
  "$1,450": "",
  "$1,500": "",
  "a + b + c = 100, b = a + 20, c = a - 10. Substitute: a + (a + 20) + (a - 10) = 100, 3a = 90, a = 30, b = 50, c = 20. Profit = 300 + 750 + 400 = $1,450.": "",
  "An investor puts $20,000 into stocks (8% return), bonds (5%), and savings (2%). Total annual return is $1,060. The amount in stocks equals the combined bonds and savings. How much is in bonds?": "",
  "$2,000": "",
  "$3,000": "",
  "$1,000": "",
  "$4,000": "",
  "s + b + v = 20000, s = b + v, so s = 10000. 0.08(10000) + 0.05b + 0.02(10000 - b) = 1060: 800 + 0.05b + 200 - 0.02b = 1060, 0.03b = 60, b = $2,000.": "",
  "A test has three sections: A, B, and C. The total is 100 points. Section A has 10 more points than C. Section B has twice as many points as C. How many points is Section A worth?": "",
  "32.5": "",
  "28.5": "",
  "40": "",
  "35": "",
  "a + b + c = 100, a = c + 10, b = 2c. Substitute: (c + 10) + 2c + c = 100, 4c = 90, c = 22.5. Section A = 22.5 + 10 = 32.5 points.": "",
  "A store sells three sizes of coffee: small ($2), medium ($3), and large ($5). On Monday, 80 cups were sold for $270. The number of smalls equaled the number of larges. How many medium cups were sold?": "",
  "20": "",
  "10": "",
  "30": "",
  "s + m + l = 80, 2s + 3m + 5l = 270, s = l. Substitute: m = 80 - 2l. Then 2l + 3(80 - 2l) + 5l = 270, l = 30, m = 20. Check: 30 + 20 + 30 = 80 and 60 + 60 + 150 = 270.": "",
  "A shipping company loads three types of packages: type A weighs 2 lbs, type B weighs 3 lbs, and type C weighs 10 lbs. A truck carries 20 packages weighing 80 lbs total. If there are equal numbers of A and B packages, how many C packages are on the truck?": "",
  "8": "",
  "Set up: a + b + c = 20, 2a + 3b + 10c = 80, a = b. Substituting a = b gives 2b + c = 20, so c = 20 - 2b. Then 5b + 10(20 - 2b) = 80, which simplifies to -15b = -120, so b = 8, a = 8, and c = 4.": "",
  "A nutritionist plans a meal with three foods. Food X has 3g protein per serving, Food Y has 5g, Food Z has 2g. The meal needs 8 servings total, 30g protein, and twice as many Y servings as Z servings. How many servings of Food X?": "",
  "Set up: x + y + z = 8, 3x + 5y + 2z = 30, y = 2z. Substituting gives x = 8 - 3z, then 3(8 - 3z) + 5(2z) + 2z = 30 simplifies to 24 + 3z = 30, so z = 2, y = 4, and x = 2 servings.": "",
  "A charity fundraiser sells three types of items: bracelets ($3), t-shirts ($10), and hats ($7). They sell 50 items for $280. The number of bracelets is 10 more than hats. How many t-shirts were sold?": "",
  "15": "",
  "25": "",
  "Set up: b + t + h = 50, 3b + 10t + 7h = 280, b = h + 10. Substituting gives t = 40 - 2h, then 3(h + 10) + 10(40 - 2h) + 7h = 280 simplifies to -10h + 430 = 280, so h = 15, b = 25, and t = 10.": ""
